      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2011 BMW M3 (E92) powered by the iconic S65 4.0L naturally aspirated V8. This high-revving powerplant is paired with a 7-speed M-DCT dual-clutch gearbox, offering seamless torque delivery and lightning-quick shifts. The vehicle features Electronic Damper Control (EDC) and a variable M differential lock for superior handling characteristics. Maintenance is current, with rod bearings and throttle actuators recently addressed to ensure the long-term reliability of the high-strung valvetrain. While showing minor aesthetic patina consistent with its age, the performance envelope remains fully intact and the chassis remains taut. A driver-focused example ready for the B-roads.",
